name: Christine S.
review_text: Very good thin crust and cauliflower crust pizzas! 3 days later I was craving it again. They even have eegee's slushes there! Not all the flavors, but enough for me to be excited about.

name: Ed D.
review_text: Delicious, great quality toppings, sturdy and friendly service.  Highly recommend when you're looking fur high wishy pizza

name: Ellen M.
review_text: Love their pizza ! Have been loyal to them for many years which is why this surprised me. Ordered a pizza & fried pickles. Pizza was cold & not prepared correctly & the pickles were over fried. When I called to bring this up, didn't speak to a manager as he/she was too busy but he/she did tell the employee to offer me a free pizza. Would be mailed. Wonderful. However when I got the coupon in the mail, it's only for dine in or carry out only - not delivering. During Covid I am not going to dine in as well as carry outs it's not in the cards for my household as we need to stay quarantined for our health. I ordered a pizza for delivery for a reason and my free coupon didn't honor that. Very disappointing

name: Brent S.
review_text: I was looking for a new place for NY Style pizza near me and decided to give Zzeek's a try and am glad I did! I tried the deluxe pizza and it was pure deliciousness - from the fresh toppings, to the sauce and the extremely crunchy crust. Highly recommend!

name: Kelley S.
review_text: As always, Zzeeks is good stuff! Perfect crust- the right amount of chewy, and the right amount of tasty ingredients served hot! I pulled up, and someone walked the order out to me the moment it was out of the oven. Chicken wings were great too!

name: Leslie M.
review_text: First and last time ordering!! Pizza was cold, burnt and not edible. Our 5 and 6 year olds didn't finish theirs. I'm very disappointed.

name: Alexis Q.
review_text: favorite pizza place ever! so many diff options and large portions for the price you pay. the slices are huge and the wings are my fav!

name: Lisa B.
review_text: Finally found the place for perfect pizza! I have ordered from Zzeeks twice. Both time pizza was exceptional thin and regular crust. Did I mention how incredible the wings are. Can't wait for the next pizza night in my house!

name: Amy Y.
review_text: We've tried several items on the menu and love them all!! The free delivery and no contact delivery options are great! We've had trouble finding a pizza place we like...so we're so grateful we found Zzeeks!!!

name: Joseph B.
review_text:
We ordered pizza and the garlic rub chicken wings and the taste and quality was excellent.  We order pizza regularly from several places trying to find a high quality and flavorful pizza and Zesty pizza and wings awesome.

I recommend this establishment!

Joe Black owner of HomeTech Appliace Repair

name: Mindy E.
review_text: I don't eat Gluten and my nephew has celiac and Zzeeks has THE BEST Gluten Free pizza! Excellent service if you do pick up and excellent service if you do delivery.  Follow Zzeeks on Facebook so you are up to date on a specials and the great things they are doing to help the community!!!!

name: Jennifer K.
review_text: We have been happy with our orders so far. Pizza has been tasty, though one time we got one that was overcooked a bit. The wings are delish. Lots of flavor choices. We have tried the typical hot sauce and garlic parmesan and liked them. We plan on ordering again when the mood strikes.

name: Kevin J.
review_text: Zzeeks Pizza is awesome. I stumbled across it one day over by Lowe's. This place has now become my pizza of choice. They also have som great wings (Cajun Rub). The staff has always been great and the service is fast.

name: Trevor T.
review_text:
Please discontinue the hard chard wine.  Served one to my wife, not good and she typically drinks any kind.

On a positive note, the wings and pizza are great!

name: Cheryl C.
review_text: This place does not disappoint!!! Management and staff on point.  Lexi took my order and was so pleasant.  Pizza and wings were so good.   Can't wait to go back!!!

name: Aaron T.
review_text:
I had really been wanting to try this place - especially since it was a local, family-owned place.  Turned out to be a total bust, unfortunately.  Noticed on their website that several of the pictures of pizzas looked like they were WELL done, but... it's kind of a sloppy website so we thought maybe it was just bad photography, and ordered anyways.  

We ordered a 16" Chicken Pesto pizza, and a Caprese salad.  Once at the restaurant, it seemed to be chaos - can't blame them entirely - COVID-19 has everything a mess, but some better signage or organization or something may help.  Anyways, paid up but our pizza wasn't ready just yet, so we stepped back and waited a few minutes.  Seems they forgot who we were or our order status, just more chaos/confusion.  No worries though, it still came out in a reasonable time.

We live 3.1 miles door to door, and the smell on the way home was amazing.  But once home and opened the pizza box, the story changed...  it looked like it had been made *hours* earlier.  It was barely even warm, and WAY overcooked.  The chicken looked like something you cooked and left on the stove for an afternoon and it got dried out.  The entire thing looked like it had been left sitting out -- had they made an extra hours ago and just slid it into a fresh cardboard box?  Or run it through the oven twice?  It's getting late, we're hungry, so dig in anyways.  Mind you this is a "Chicken Pesto" pizza - the pesto was a few mere traces here and there; neither of us could taste the pesto whatsoever and had to dig around looking for any sign of it.  The entire pizza - crust and ingredients - were extremely dry and bland.  Definitely no "zest" on this pie.  

The Caprese Salad...  An absolute joke.  The three slices of under-ripe tomato were haphazardly cut WAY too thick and looked to be cut by someone wearing a blindfold and using a butter knife.  There was ONE piece of basil on top.  HUH?!?!  Basil is a key ingredient in Caprese, not a garnish.  And they served it with a packet of balsamic vinaigrette salad dressing, not a balsamic reduction.  

It's practically unheard of me to refer to anything with cheese in it as "awful," but both this pizza and Caprese salad were absolutely awful.  This place is on the pricey side, so I certainly expect better than this.  I gave them a shot, but I'll stick with the other nearby places in the future.

name: Taegan P.
review_text: I always enjoy ordering pizza take out from Zzeeks. Their employees are always kind when picking up and the food always tastes great. Their wings are also fantastic. Overall, this place really just doesn't disappoint.

name: Eva P.
review_text:
This was my first time at Zzeeks. I had heard good things about it.  I don't recommend it.
1. I ordered online and it said my order would be ready in 15 minutes.  Since I was 15 minutes away, that was perfect. We will call this time O for Order.
2. I arrive at O+18 minutes.  I'm waiting for someone to get off the phone. I see my pizza.
3.  At O+21 minutes, someone points out that the person is still on the phone and can someone help the people waiting.
4.  At O+23 minutes I am told my pizza is ready but my EGs is not and it shouldn't be more than 5 minutes.
5.  At O+27 minutes, I see someone holding my EGs passing me by. Then, finally the person helping me intercepts the EGs and gives it to me.
6.  At O+30 minutes I am in my car eating pizza because I'm hungry, but it is already no longer hot.
7. At O+36 minutes, I am home eating room temperature pizza.  
8. At O+37 minutes, I decide the pizza isn't even that great and I won't go back.
Thank you!

name: Secret S.
review_text:
"Super Sorry"

Well, I have to say I'm disappointed in ZZ tonight.
Since they opened we've been patrons and thought the world of them when they opened up their pantry to the community during grocery store shortages. For this, I'm not giving them the 1-Star review that they deserved for their counter service, their food quality, and lack of  customer service .

I noticed there was a deal today where The Husband and Wife Law team would be picking up half the bill.
Great!
I called in my order. The young man tells me it's going to be $73. I inquire about the "deal" and he tells me the deal was earlier and it was already o er (?)
Okay.
I go ahead with the order because we're hungry and I'm not that cheap of an a*hole that the order hinged on this deal. But it was still a bummer.
I tip ahead of time (20% of $73). The young man says it'll be 35 mins for it to be delivered.
An hour and ten minutes later, I call to ask where the order was and the same young man tells me, "Oh well thats weird because its showing its been delivered." I assure him that whatever screen he's looking at is mistaken. He ponders a few options, goes through my address, name, etc..again before saying he's going to get a manager to help me out.
A minute or so later the young man gets on the phone, (not the manager), and says, "I'm SUPER SORRY. I don't know what happened, maybe we skipped over yours but we're going to get it out to you right away; like 15 mins."
Pizza arrived 15 mins later, as promised. No acknowledgment from the young lady about the botched order.
Get the pizza into the kitchen and find dried out,  semi-warm pizza that was definitely left sitting for a while.
The wings also tasted like their fryer oil needed to be changed.

So......

I love how they worked with the community. I love their Keto options. I love that they offer growlers.

But......

Their service tonight SUCKED. The management missed the opportunity to make a piss-poor experience any better by remaking my pizza or discounting my order due to their mess up. So I'm SUPER SORRY but I can't support businesses like that.

Buh-Bye, Zeeks!

name: Add D.
review_text: I love Zzeeks not only for the fantastic pizza but, the people who work there. So thankful for them during this time. Jody constantly is finding new ways to help the community out from the pizza specials to 50% off courtesy of the husband and wife law team. Their staff work their butts off day in and day out. Hope the rest of the community can be a little more patient especially when zzeeks is having a special deal going on

name: Mike G.
review_text: Updated review: the Owner reached out to me, turns out that the delivery driver forgot one of our pizza's on our order. That stuff happens, and had he just been honest and said that, we would have still been disappointed as it was a birthday party, but understood the reason it took forever. That said, owner sent out a gift card and was completely honest with us. Shee definately was understanding and apologetic as well. That meant a lot to our family as not all places are honest with you.  I'll change my rating back to 5 star as the pizza and wings are top notch...great family owned business to support. Thank you for great food and better customer service.

name: K D.
review_text:
Zzeeks had made a post during the Covid-19 crises that despite restaurants being allowed to open their dining rooms, they decided to keep their staff and customers safe by continuing to offer curbside pick up and FREE delivery. I had always wanted to try Zzeek's (hadn't because we are too far for delivery), but their post promoted my family to support their business. When I got there, one of their oven had broken. With the exception of one or two irrational selfish customers, most everyone was supportive and understanding. Yes, I may have had to wait and extra 30 minutes (if that's the worst thing in someone's life, you have an amazing life), but my pizza was fresh and my entire order correct. The staff was going out of their way to be friendly, and offered everyone free drinks. Upon getting home, my whole family was very pleased! This pizza was so flavorful and the ratios of cheese and sauce were perfect!

We will be new regulars to Zzeeks. Hopefully they put one in a bit farther east, but until then, I guess I'll make the drive.

name: William L.
review_text: Zzeeks did a curbside pick-up event for $5 cheese pizza. The routing for the event was pretty confusing as people were cutting in line etc but with the turnout somewhat expected. Once I eventually reached the front they had it pretty organized and the service was super nice. I ordered 2 of the cheese pizzas only but they also were selling other items as well. The cheese pizza was smaller than I expected however it was tasty and had a nice crispy crust. The cheese was extra "cheesy" which was amazing as well. Overall, for the $5 amount is a good price but a tad smaller than I was expecting. Great small business and nice employees, however looking at their regular prices for the pizzas (think it's $12 for this same pizza normally) it is priced at the upper end. I would give the place a try if you're looking for something locally but definitely leverage deals as the regular prices feel high.

name: Dan F.
review_text:
The pizza here was actually pretty good. The sauce is a little spicier than I like, but that's why they call it Zesty Zzeeks. The service though was really bad two times in a row.
The first time, they delivered wings which came with absolutely no sauce on them. Just plain, fried wings. What? So I called and the employee said he would check on it and call me back in 5-10 minutes. 30 minutes later, no call, so I called back. To his credit, he was on his way with the wings, But he never called back to let me know. We did get replacement wings about an hour after the pizza.

Tonight I called in Pizza and wings and they said it would be ready for pick up in 15 minutes. I was there 15 minutes later and they could not find my order. Then they found it, but I don't think they started on it because I was there for another 30 min. OK, things happen, but usually a manager will come out and apologize or maybe offer you an appetizer... Nope. He left it to the poor 17-year-old girl at the front desk to apologize. It was very warm in there so I asked for a glass of water and he said he'd have to charge me for the Styrofoam cup... This is after being 20 minutes late with the pizza. But the nice girl found a glass and gave me some ice water.  Other customers were having the same late pizza problem. This clearly was not a very experienced manager. The place seemed hectic and unorganized.  I felt really bad for the staff.

name: Andy L.
review_text: We love this place. The cauliflower pizza is great and so is the regular pizza. The wings & house salad are yummy too. If you get a chance to have their Zzeeks beer on draft it's pretty good too.

name: Hanh N.
review_text:
I tired Zzeeks for the first time tonight and I was disappointed.  I felt like wings and Zzeeks was very close and I wanted to supper local business.  I thought Sunday special was $0.60 wings, but I was charged regular price.  I'm okay with that, but the quality wasn't worth what I paid. The fried zucchini was greasy and over priced. The staff was friendly but I'll go elsewhere if I have a craving for wings
I didn't know you would be charged for ranch with my order or wings and zucchini. I received more ranch than I needed. I think customer should be notified if they are being charged for ranch, or build that into the cost.
I wish your business success, but I don't think I'll try Zzeeks again

name: Adam A.
review_text: We just tried Zesty Zzeeks Pizza Ocotillo for our first time a few weeks ago and we're already back for more. We had with the hand tossed pepperoni pizza and bone in hot wings made extra crispy. Delicious both times, this is our new go to pizza joint! My only wish is that the place was a bit bigger as they have limited inside seating and due to the fact that it's so delicious, the place is packed. They do have outdoor tables, which are great before the weather gets hot. If you're plan is to eat out for pizza, this could be a consideration, but the food is great and take out from Zzeeks is on point!

name: Jessica H.
review_text: Best thin crust pizza we have found outside of Chicago. Had a issue with an order but they went above and beyond to make it right.  During these crazy times they are also going above and beyond for the community. Thank you so much

name: Jason L.
review_text:
We've had Zzeeks Pizza twice now and it's been excellent both times. I'm from Long Island, NY and it's as close to NY pizza as you're going to get. Especially, the Brooklyn style crust. Not too thin and not too thick. I highly recommend their pizza. Haven't had anything else so can't comment on the rest of the menu.

I would give 5 stars but there are a couple of things they can improve on. First, only offering the Brooklyn crust in a 20" isn't ideal considering it's just my wife and I and the 20" is HUGE. It could feed 6 adults easy. They really need to offer the Brooklyn in smaller options.

Lastly, the app is easy to order but there's no option to view your order or past orders once you've hit submit. Seems like an easy fix.

name: Jonathan S.
review_text: Exceptional pizza, friendly staff and good beers including a collab brew with Odell. Super impressed with the no carb crust that is just as good as just about any thin crust. Highly recommend

name: Morgan P.
review_text:
3-7-20 update;
Things have improved.  I was really enjoying their NY style but now that the store has its legs under it, the pies have improved.  Toppings are dense, crust crispy yep chewy with a slight tang.  Very very good, people that work there are going for it - I appreciate the vibe.

This is by far the best pizza in the Ocotillo area.  I really like how they cater to the keto diet crowd, the crust less pizza bowl is a slam dunk.  It's in a pie tin with cheese, sauce and some toppings.  

Wings are perfect-o.  I get them well done and with a dry rub.  do the delivery thru , so the wings show up super lava hot.

name: Victoria R.
review_text: I just tried their cauliflower pizza for the first time and it was delicious! I never would have known it wasn't normal pizza crust! So good!!!

name: Martin T.
review_text: Just discovered Zzeeks today!! I have been Keto for 2 years and they have a Keto Pizza Crust! It was incredible!! Thanks so much for the awesome food and free delivery.

name: Jane J.
review_text: Pizza was ok, very dark brown, probably could've spent a little less time in oven.  We ordered a 10 piece wing, got 2 different flavors and they charged us more for that. Guy on phone said no xtra charge...but there is. Bummed, thought this place would be our go to since it's close.

name: Layke A.
review_text: I wanted to try Zzeeks because their menu looked interesting. It went downhill from there. The pizza was decent, but after waiting over an hour to have it delivered, it was cold. I called the restaurant to find out what happened to my pizza and was told they were very busy at the store. When the delivery guy finally showed up, an hour and 15 minutes after I placed my order, he said his car broke down. Somebody needs to get their story straight. The guy I spoke with on the phone didn't even care that I had waited over an  hour for a pizza to arrive that was supposed to take no longer than a 35 minutes. Very bad customer service. My cold 12" "Meat" pizza cost $22.00. It wasn't worth it. There are lots of pizza places in this area with better hot pizza and FAR better service.

name: Beth S.
review_text: We tried this place for the first time tonight.  I ordered online and I must have clicked on something wrong when ordering my beef sandwich.  They called me to make sure I wanted ground beef and not sliced beef.  I did not!  So glad they caught it and called to verify before making it.  Delivery arrived a little earlier than scheduled.  Food was hot.  My husband loves spicy food.  The hotter the better. He got their suicide wings with double sauce.  They were the hottest wings he has ever eaten. He has a hard time finding places that make stuff as hot as he likes so I know we will be ordering from them again.  Maybe next time try their pizza.

name: Aaron A.
review_text:
Super freakin good wings and beer prices are crazy cheap.
Coming from ASU area and definitely worth the trip.
Was recommended the angry mustard flavored wings and loved the taste of them! Great service too.

name: Trevor S.
review_text: Waited 30 minutes for eegees. 30 minutes. For drinks. Restaurant was barely half full. Will not bring my business here again.

name: Scott M.
review_text:
I was a consistent customer of Jets Pizza located across the street and have found myself leaning to Zesty Zzeeks over the last few weeks for our family Friday night pizza.

Delivery was fast. The delivery guy knocked on my door like the sheriffs department serving a warrant.

Review updated. FREE DELIVERY!!!!!!

name: Nova H.
review_text:
What a great little restaurant.

Staff was friendly and welcoming. Food order was prompt.

Ordered a salad, cheese curds, and a sandwich.

Salad was out in less than 5 minutes. Cheese curds shortly after. Had to let them sit for a minute as they were piping hot. The breading on them was light and delicious!  

Sandwich arrived shortly after. The bread was toasty. Cheese was melting. And the chicken on it was plentiful.

I loved that the staff walks around to make sure every customer was happy.

Started getting busy but you wouldn't know if. Staff handled all the customers quickly.

They informed us of an upcoming fundraiser and invited us back. We plan on returning sooner than later.

name: Jamie H.
review_text: Love their pizza and wings! I wish that they delivered to my house as their actual space is kinda small. Decent service as well.

name: Christina K.
review_text: The owners are fantastic and the food is so good. I love supporting family owned businesses..They made my sons 12th Birthday the best "birthday ever". My son and his friends were brought into the back to make their pizzas. They absolutely loved this experience and talked about it all night! Thank you so much!

name: Laurie L.
review_text: First time trying this place and love it! We ordered for delivery and the service, start to finish was A+. The order process on the phone, my husband spoke to Jody and she had a friendly voice and quickly took our order and thanked my husband when he had his CC info ready The delivery guy was really nice and very prompt! We ordered a regular pepperoni pizza (super excited about trying the keto crust pizza) and a dry rub wing (which was delicious), and a honey BBQ. (We much preferred the dry rub). Definitely will order again and refer to family and friends!

name: Boomer B.
review_text:
We used this location for takeout pizza tonight.  I can't imagine returning.

The ingredients are just average in quality, like Domino's, with a few, like the Canadian bacon, being far below average.   Two of our girls had ham on their pizza and they both said it smelled like old rubber.

We placed an online order for 3 pizzas with a scheduled pickup time of 45 minutes later. The online system said it could be ready in as little as 15 minutes.

So we arrived at our pickup time and it was going to be just another 5-7 minutes.  After 15 minutes, we asked again, and it was "just another 5-7 minutes" yet again.

During this process, 1 of 3 pizzas was sitting in the heating are the whole time.  Another came out about halfway through.  The 3rd was out about 20 minutes after the scheduled pickup time.  

We felt bad for another guy waiting for his 4 pizzas, 3 of which sat under the heating element for the entire time we were there.

If I were running a pizza place and orders were this far behind, I would have offered guests a $5 or $10 off coupon on the next order.  

The physical layout of the restaurant is bad - staff are continually busting through the customer waiting line, carrying pizza from the right or beverage orders from the left.  Staff were rather rude as they pushed us out of the way.

They sprayed some industrial cleaner on the tables to clean and disinfect them.  I appreciate that, but the smell was awful - I lost my appetite while waiting.

When we first arrived, it took the cashier several minutes to find our order.  She tried telling us we hadn't ordered from them.  I spelled my name for her three times and she looked me up using the wrong spelling each time. Finally, she found us.

It took one cashier 10 minutes to take a phone order, while the rest of us waited in line - without a second cashier coming forward until the end of that 10 minutes.  

This all reflects on management, the physical design of the restaurant, and the quality of ingredients from corporate.

name: Maricela C.
review_text: I first started going to Zzeeks at the Ahwatukee location, when I worked at Chuck E. Cheese. This was the go to spot to eat. I ended up moving to chandler in 2017 and saw this location by my work. I recognized one of the cooks that came into my job, and he offered me free pizza/breadsticks. Zzeeks pizza is bomb!! They are  a great company, always make you feel  like family. (:

name: Tom E.
review_text: We were desperately seeking jalapeño poppers.  Google, Siri, Alexa were no help at all.  By chance found Zzeeks web site!  Very good Jalapeño poppers.  10 minute drive, less than five minutes later we had them. Planning to try more of the menu soon.

name: Brendan D.
review_text:
I found this place through a yelp search, and found out it was a new spot for pizza. Definitely pricier than the average pizza, but the flavors are worth it.

My only disappointment was the pizza dough wasn't cooked fully. I order their "Meats" pizza on a double/thick dough, and near the center the dough was  undercooked. So luckily after 8-10 minutes in my oven it came out fine. But overall I will go back again.

name: Terry P.
review_text: Stopped in for the first time to dine in.  First thing we noticed was the noise level.  We almost left, but since it just opened in the neighborhood we though we'd deal with it.  We ordered the 12" extreme pepperoni pizza on their medium crust.  The person taking the order seemed to be in a rush when we wanted an explanation of the types of crust... made it real confusing.  She also wanted to know what kind of additional sauce we wanted.  She quickly rattled off a list until we said garlic.  We sat down at a table... a employee dropped off a small container of garlic/butter sauce... had no clue what that was for.  Then we looked at our bill and was charged 75 cents for this little container of garlic/butter sauce.  There was no mentioned that this was an extra cost or even what it was.  We were a bit irritated at the "up-sale".  The pizza was just okay, but the noise level meant we won't be back.

name: Marie B.
review_text:
The latest addition to world pizza domination. We went to this newest Zzesty Zeek's location to celebrate my birthday. It was very different than the other locations. Seemed smaller, but it was still good. I got the pepperoni that has many different options of pepperoni put all on one pizza. It is totally greasy, never have found a pepperoni that is not, but I use towels to sop up the grease and enjoy.

Good luck Zeek! On to Wold Domination!

name: Kelly G.
review_text: Great wings and even greater pizza. Chill atmosphere. Staff is friendly and helpful. Great restaurant at a great location.

name: Mike D.
review_text: I thought it was a bit overpriced. Not much inside seating. Wings were kind of undercooked and fatty. Pizza was good. The specials seem to be a better deal, but you can't get a giant slice of any of the specialty pizzas.

name: Derek Y.
review_text:
Wasn't great food but wasn't bad. Place was really busy so that's great that we have other options in food that hopefully can stick in this plaza.

Fried pickles were the best of what we ordered. Breading was nice and crunchy. Pizza was average. Buffalo chicken sandwich didn't have much that made me think about buffalo chicken. No breading. Not spicy. That was the low ranking item.

I will give it another chance.

name: David M.
review_text: Definitely ignore the first person that reviewed this place. Their pizza is so good. This brand new pizza restaurant has a very welcoming decor for families alike. From what I've heard, their wings are phenomenal too - will have to give them a try!

name: Michael R.
review_text: This place is great. Great location nice big screen tvs to watch football, great staff with great customer service and most importantly the food was amazing. We have been to the other zzeeks locations and the food never seems to disappoint. The owner was awesome she came out said hi made sure we were taken care of and made sure our good tasted excellent. They have an awesome patio and a nice bar inside as well. This is a place to come on your own or bring the kids and the family. Alot of space inside and outside. We will definitely be back.

name: Marian B.
review_text: Fantastic!!! Very nice location,  clean,  friendly and fabulous food!!  Perfect place for football!!!

name: Eddie K.
review_text:
Holy cow, what a beautiful restaurant, amazing food, and wonderful staff. So happy to have one here in our area now! Love the food, always fresh and flavorful, and the menu is so wide ranging I never get burnt out on their food.

They have $3.50 20 Oz beers every day, and they have some primo beers my friends! 60¢ wings on Sundays. Free delivery! Did I mention, free delivery???

As great as all the above is, the best part about supporting Zzeeks is how much they give back to the community. Just amazing people who know what being a part of the community is all about.

name: D W.
review_text: This place is bran spanking new, Clean and beautiful!! Zzeeks has the best pizza, wings, and Service... its family owned and operated. They offer something for everyones special diets keto, gluten, ect..The owners go out of there way to make you feel at home..

name: Christine M.
review_text: Second time trying this place! Their wings are delicious! Dry rub cajun is the way to go! Pizza is good, chicken tenders and fries are good too! Definitely will be back and have told friends about it.

name: Gwen M.
review_text: Dont waste your time. After waiting months for this place to open,  thinking its gonna be the new 'it place', turns out is a dump.

name: Jason Cooper
review_text: The pizza and wings were delicious. They delivered my food in a timely manner. I would highly recommend this restaurant!

name: Nelson Slater
review_text: It was my first time here, and they got a new returning customer! The food was tasty, and the customer service was excellent. Food was cooked and seasoned just to perfection. It is our new pizza place without any hesitation.

name: Jules Nativio
review_text: I have been waiting to leave this review until after the lockdown was lifted as I did not want to affect any business for them. I ordered Zeeks lot from the Chandler ( warner) location.  However, the last time I ordered in March, a liter of Pespi was delivered instead if Diet Pepsi.  Not a big deal and driver told me he would adjust my bill. No problem. Two days later, I called up Zeeks as the adjustment never occured.  Whoever I spoke to acted as if I did something wrong. He had an attitude and was rude. He said he could not adjust the bill (credit to my debit card) the day after a transaction. I've never heard of this lack of fucntionality. He told me he could not add a credit to my account.  He told me he could not note my account for future orders. Instead, he could mail me a gift card.  I asked if I could pick it up.  He said it has to be mailed.  Weird but okay.  Well I never received the gift card and have not ordered Zeeks since. I was ordering from then once a week, so their loss.  Good pizza though and owner seems very cool. Actually came out on a delivery once.

name: David Goodman
review_text: Love their pizza.

name: Jenna G
review_text: Zesty Zzeeks is what's up! Ordered last night for the first time and was pleasantly surprised! Delivery was fast and contact-less, and pizza was hot! It was delicious, even the gluten free, and that's always a gamble. We found our new pizza spot!

name: Mark Jordan
review_text: Great pizza and wings!! Love them!!

name: Hunter Huisken
review_text: I have ordered food from two locations over the past couple years, and this establishment without a doubt, is best service in pizza

name: Leehawk NewMoon
review_text: New York style pizza was overcooked almost no cheese fr

name: Chance Houston
review_text: Avoid! Does not enforce posted mask policy. Did not clean counter surfaces after mask-less customer used card reader. It’s a free country, get your pizza somewhere else.

name: Aaron Simmons
review_text: Wings were just ok tonight. Pizza you can tell has been sitting in the heating area it was rock hard. Also, dont ask for tip over the phone before the product is delivered. It is unfortunate because it's so close to the house. It feels like they have been getting worse, they used to be awesome. We had a similar problem a few months ago. The manager was very apologetic and was supposed to send some coupons which never showed up. We dont want anything free just want it to be correct so not looking for anything. We dont usually review online because we know the reputational damage it can cause but, in this case and past performance it was warranted.

name: Mia Perkins
review_text: The pizza here is amazing. And the boneless wings....dont get me started . Juicy flavorful and you can just eat one! Amd why would you! They also have a few flavors of Eegees and coming from Tucson i have missed Eegees!

name: Niqui Kukel
review_text: Not the quality I was expecting for the price. Mediocre at best... Maybe the dine in experience paid better homage to their pricing? Sad to say even with .70 wing special we will not be going back.

name: Josh
review_text: Wings were pretty good. Only thing is I wish they were more crispy. Nice big juicy wings with plenty of ranch dipping sauce.

name: Dean Doherty
review_text: Pretty typical of what passes for pizza in the Phx metro.  Unremarkable Dominoes-like sauce, original crust ok, average amount of toppings, no real distinctive flavor.  A pizza.  And an average one at best.  One level above Dominoes/PJohns.  Poor value imo given price.

name: Kayla Koglmeier
review_text: My little one and I always come and get Eegee's and the staff are ALWAYS super polite, respectful, and friendly. We love coming here. Thank you guys for being awesome!

name: monika letzte
review_text: This is truly an amazing place for grub the staff are all kind and work hard on delivering high quality food for their costumers. I rate 5 stars the food is a wide variety and delicious

name: Antonio RIVERA
review_text: Love the pizza also the wings are great mango habanero is my favorite. And reasonably  priced. Plus they have beer!🤘

name: melissa scotty
review_text: Great staff. Great food

name: Paula Armenta
review_text: First time there and was very disappointed. Won't be going back.

name: Desiree Sherant
review_text: Pizza and wings are very good! Great customer service too. I messed up placing my online order (selected boneless when I wanted bone-in) they without fuss or anything made me a new order of wings the way I wanted it and gave me the messed up wings as well.

name: john hobbs
review_text: Good pizza but don't order the Chicken sub

name: Jayden E
review_text: I love their food but this is crazy. It’s very inconsistent. We order cauliflower wings all the time but most time we only get a few pieces now. Today was the worst yet ever. Paid 7.99 for just 9 small cauliflower. I cannot believe it. I won’t be ordering again.  Once we made two orders of them and one had 10 pieces and the other had about 15. I don’t understand.

name: Krista McKinney
review_text: The pizza and wings are amazing!   I have no picture because we ate it too fast.  Delivery was exactly when they said it would be.  The owners are very community minded and have been selling bread flour and yeast and other staples at their cost during the covid pandemic.  I appreciate their care for the community in keeping the dining rooms closed until it's safe to reopen.

name: Keshaundra
review_text: I was just here yesterday and my wings were so hard that I couldn’t bite into them. I ordered garlic Parmesan and couldn’t even taste the seasoning at all. Very disappointed in this because two days before I had wings and they were amazing.

name: Michelle Brungardt
review_text: We read about Zesty Zzeeks in the paper and had decided we wanted to try it, although we live in the West Valley.  We were amazed!  We ordered the Margherita and Grand Slam pizzas on St Louis Thin crust...I never knew pizza could taste that fresh and amazing.  The crust was perfect and each pizza had plenty of toppings.  This won't be our last visit!

name: Julie Shade
review_text: We’ve never eaten here yet… I just want to give you guys a shoutout… During the whole quarantine you guys sold supplies… That’s pretty stellar of what you did! Can’t wait to try you guys out someday soon.

name: Cory Chapman
review_text: I just got a good pizza.  From an extrovert. In the middle of a global pandemic. Guy shows up, ignores request to leave pie outside, is wearing a bandana, directly ignores me standing back and asking to leave pie on recycle bin, wants to have a five minute conversation about stray cats.

name: Jesse Heimann
review_text: Wings are the BEST! We love honey barbecue, but just discovered the place so working our way through the sauces! Pizza rocks too, but one of these times we're going to try some of their gluten free, keto pizzas.

name: Alex S
review_text: At 7:12 PM I called and placed an order for delivery and was told 45 minutes (documented call).At 8:35 PM  I called about the non-delivered order, and was told "the driver just left with that order (documented call).At 8:58 PM I called about the non-delivered order (documented call).  The employee said they couldn't find any record of any order.  After several iterations of going over location and phone numbers to verify details, the employee called me a liar and hung up on me.At 9:04 PM I called back to request the owners names, and the employee said he would hand up on me again (documented call).  I obtained the owner's names.At 9:12 my phone rings - It's Zeek's, a manager, telling me "they checked their phone system and found all my calls, but lost my order."   You don't say?During a time when restaurants should be doing everything, this employee(s) is losing orders, lying about orders being en route, in turn calling customers liars, and, saving the best for last - threatening finishing off the interaction by hanging up on them.   Oh, and then threatening to do it all again.-- Insane ---My recommendation is immediate drug testing for all employees.  I suspect this would result in the necessary final outcome of a (mostly) new staff.  Thankfully the evening manager was sane and polite.

name: Isaac Nib
review_text: Bad deals and they steal others recipe

name: Tristan Labadie
review_text: I'm not sure when you decided to make your thin crust a domino's wannabe. That was the most disappointing thing I have ever seen when I opened the pizza box up.

name: Mark H
review_text: The best

name: Jordan Webb
review_text: Horrible place

name: Jason SCANLON
review_text: The owners are awesome. Thank you for all you do for the community! They have offered supplies to the general public in a time of need. There were so many people behaving badly while  you were doing a good deed, it makes me lose faith in humanity. Thank you for kindness and generosity and for putting up with the few bad apples for the chance to help the the rest of us.

name: mitch kassel
review_text: Their gf boneless wings are really good. May be the only spot I know that offers them

name: Tandy Giefer
review_text: Took my elderly parents and two dogs to pick up a margarita pizza and bag of zeppollis  last night at ZZeeks pizza in Chandler, first time trying the place.  We opened my hatchback and had a picnic in almost empty parking lot.  Both were a 10!  Thank you for being open, and will order again.  Looking forward to being on that patio.  Hope you are dog friendly!!  Delicious!  Remember to tip these hardworking people, no matter what!!’

name: Brent Simonson
review_text: This is LITERALLY the 6th or 7th time I've had to send a salad back AFTER I ORDERED IT WITH NOOOOOOO OLIVES!!! They pre-make salads and "take out" the ingredient you ask them too. Zero attention to detail with EVERY SALAD I've ordered. If you have allergies to an ingredient, make your own salad. The pizza is FANTASTIC as usual, just please pay attention to your customers and their needs.

name: Natalie Seder
review_text: Good place for a cheap, quick and tasty lunch! Best bread sticks!!!! If you don't believe me, try them for yourself.

name: T Gilmore
review_text: Man this is good pizza!!  I love the different options for crust, everything has so much flavor and its not very greasy.  The service was really good and the owners are so friendly.  Great place!

name: Melinda Roberts
review_text: Great tasting pizzas.

name: Barry Graziano
review_text: Employees were pleasant. We ordered chicken Philly cheese steak, fried zuchinni, 10 pice regular bone in wings, and fries. They bought us a chicken parm. Apologetic and left the chicken parm for us and made the chicken philly. We came here for the wings, heard they were great. Disappointing...very very small, smallest wings I have every seen,  and appeared over cooked. Tasted okay..underwhelming, not worth price. The pizza looked really good, I should have ordered that instead. I really liked the crust options offered, cauliflower and gluten free. Kudos for this, I wish I had tried them instead of the wings. I would go back and try the pizza.

name: james davidson
review_text: The low carb keto options are delicious ! The have an amazing broccoli cheddar crust!

name: Megan Van Damme
review_text: We saw this when driving by one day and we are a family of hardcore pizza eaters so naturally wanted to try it out. I ordered online and had it delivered. We loved the sound of a lot of pizzas but got two specialty pizzas in one. We also ordered a small pizza for our kids that have a flavor profile that only accepts cheese. This pizza was absolutely outstanding! I cannot wait to order more and work my way through the menu. I will HAPPILY order from them again. Delivery was prompt, pizza was fresh (and delicious), and the prices were reasonable. Seriously, if you haven't had it, definitely give it a try! I can't wait to try the wings! Consider us future repeat customers :)

name: Charlie Cabot
review_text: Great pizza and wings

name: April Nye
review_text: We've tried the cauliflower pizza in the past and it was delicious! It is limited to a 10" however so that's a bummer. Tonight we tried out the 2x Dough and it did not disappoint. Have not eaten inside the restaurant, only had delivery. Both times were quick and pizza was exactly as ordered. Very impressed and will recommend to friends 👍

name: Brandi Rodriguez
review_text: Good pizza

name: Xavier Starr
review_text: Went in early today a bought a pizza only to take it home and found hairs! I have ate here on a couple occasion and I have never found hairs on top of that I wasn't helped as fast as I normally do and it wasn't even busy!! I used to love this place but I might reconsider eating somewhere else.

name: kim gaworski
review_text: Best wings ever , and prompt delivery! Most sauces are wayyyy to spicy for me but even without, best I’ve had hands down! Delivered pizza was not good, comparable to the one you can pick up for $5.00.

name: GamesDream
review_text: I walked in around 5-6 today and the place was over crowded and not a family environment!! RUDE STAFF!! Customer service was horrible if non existent! I tried to go in for a simple meal with the family and wasn't greeted so we left.. will not be coming back anytime soon!

name: AG'S Reviews
review_text: Extremely rude! My husband and I had ordered a day ago from here. We called because we wanted to try and give them another shot. My pizza bowl tasted off. Now this place is expensive as it is. So we wanted a refund or a replacement. A girl on the phone told my husband with an extremely bad attitude that no one could help us and wouldn't even hand the dang phone to a manager like we had requested. We called back an hour later and we finally got to talk to the manager. He was also extremely rude. He implyed we didn't actually buy anything when we would show proof of our repcipet but threw it away in THERE trash by the way. We have the charge on our bank account so don't try and play that bull that we didn't buy from here. He wasn't even budging to try and help. Definitely WILL NOT be coming back here ever again.

name: John S
review_text: Food was good. Reasonably priced.  The atmosphere was a little lacking. I figured since it was a dine in type of place they'd have at least some music playing in background. Overall not bad.

name: Ada Ayala
review_text: The wings order was wrong,I ordered hot and I didn't get them

name: A Ski
review_text: Great fast delivery. Yummy food.

name: Anthony Shepherd
review_text: Great people great food!

name: Doug Louton
review_text: Doesn't matter if I eat in or get my food delivered, everything is always just as ordered, happy friendly staff.

name: Laurie McGill
review_text: Had a delicious salad and really loved the quality and flavor of my slice.

name: Natalie Garner
review_text: Their pizza is good, but the customer service has gotten terrible. They totally got my order wrong and after I drove back and waited for them to remake it, it was wrong again and they offered me nothing for my trouble! When the manager brought out the third pizza I told him I had placed my order two hours earlier and asked for my money back even though they had finally gotten it right. He did and so I am changing my review from 1 star to 3, but please still work on your service!

name: Marilyn Danks
review_text: Huge fan of Zeeks in Ahwatukee and Tempe. Thought this location would have the same level of service and quality, but this was a disappointing experience. For being a Friday slower than I would expect Friday night, it was irritating that to dine in, it took over 45 minutes to get a pizza and gluten free wings. During that extend wait time, a customer came in with her previously picked up pizza and I overheard her saying that her daughter isn’t supposed to eat gluten, and the cauliflower crust pizza she had ordered came out as a normal dough pizza but she didn’t catch it until after her daughter had already eaten a piece. This is so horrible because my husband is celiac and their caution with food preparation is one of the reasons we love this chain. Whether it’s a lack of training or just carelessness on the part of the employees, it was not okay. Won’t be visiting this location again.

name: Devin Schnackenberg
review_text: We are frequent customers. Never had a bad experience or a bad pizza. If there were somewhere that could out Pizza the Hut.. this is it.

name: Karen Peterson
review_text: Great food and very nice workers

name: Moriah Morgan
review_text: On Sundays this place has a SUPER great sale on wings. Which, by the way, their wings are TO DIE FOR. I also came here while pregnant to pick up food for everyone, and one of the workers helped me carry all of it out to my car. They were so sweet and made sure I got inside the car safely and everything. Also, my absolute favorite pizza from here is the margherita pizza. Oh. My. God. DELICIOUS. We go as often as we can and plan to go there soon. Must try!

name: steve
review_text: Excellent pizza and appetizers, and always well staffed so the wait times are usually minimal. Super friendly and clean pizza spot!

name: Mike Myers
review_text: Best Family owned Pizzeria in the Valley! I've been a customer at Awatukee  for years Best lunch special around.   Now that Chandler is open on Arizona Ave by my house, my family is a huge fan as well.  BBQ chicken pizza yum ! Love the Pepperoni  that cups up old school style #BestPizza

name: Serena Pruett
review_text: Love this place! Always fast and friendly service. Anytime you are there waiting every single  employee that sees you will ask if you've been helped or need anything while you are waiting. Zzeeks has made me a big fan of cauliflower crust, I just might like it better than traditional crust, the crunch and flavor are amazing.

name: Jimmy Reyes
review_text: I really liked the wings. The pizza also very good. The pricing was reasonable. The staff was very friendly.

name: Amanda Schultz
review_text: Keto pizza was soooooooooooo good! So glad I found this place while here for work.

name: Melanie Chryshelle
review_text: Best pizza in town!! 🤗

name: Samuel Dudding
review_text: Love zeeks good delivery thank you guys for hooking me up

name: Devin Shinn
review_text: Got the pizza and wings, great quality:portion:price ratio. Will definitely be back.

name: Tim Grijalva
review_text: Love Zesty Zzeeks!!! Their cauliflower pizza crust is the bomb!!! Quick,  orders always correct and super yummy! One of our "Go-to's!"

name: Sayali Shetye’s Music
review_text: the pizza slices are two small

name: Niffer P
review_text: We’d heard so many reviews about the food and customer service at this place, so finally tried it today for dinner.  I don’t know what all the hubbub is about: our whole experience was really just average.  We had minimal interactions with any staff who were your average friendly: nothing I’d consider “great”.  The food (pizza and cheese curds) was decent, not great, and quite expensive for what we got.  Nothing that made us want to go back again.

name: Zachary Neeley
review_text: I really enjoy this place! The staff is friendly, and the food is pleasant. My gripe would be that the place is slightly unclean. Great for take out and delivery though!

name: Jason Achee
review_text: We tried Zzeeks for the first time about a year ago. The regular crust pizza is good but we do like Venezia's better. The reason I am still giving them 5 stars is their crust options. We love their broccoli/cheddar crust, and their cauliflower crust is good also. Having their nutritional values for their crusts listed is great! We eat pizza a lot, every week, so having a lower carb option has been great! Unfortunately this year my fiancee found out she has an autoimmune disorder and the doctors want her to do low carb(keto), and now we notice Zzeeks has Keto crust!!!   The Keto crust is my least favorite of their alternative crusts, but it isn't bad and we will gladly order it again. Now we just need to find out if any of their crusts are gluten free because now her doctors are telling her to cut gluten out also....

name: Jesus Portillo
review_text: I had a bit of snafu with my order but they ended up correcting it. Great service to go along with the great food.

name: Mariano Raigo
review_text: Good pizza
